      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KINGSBRAE BRETT (2) has some solid form under his belt and proved too strong last time to win by 3.5 lengths at this track in a handy 34.88 beating DAYSEA'S SHELLY. Goes well out of this box with a win and three minor placings. Great chance again. MY BOY BINGO (1) recorded two placings in a row before an overdue win last time, scoring by 4 lengths (34.97) at this track. Recorded one of the quickest times on the card in scoring last start. Deserves serious consideration again. CUMBRIA JACK (4) was an impressive winner last time in quickest of the meeting when scoring by 10 lengths (34.23) at this track. Harder here but will be in this for a long way. PAX BOSTONIA (3) did a good job to finish second last time out over 600m at this track (35.10) in a OPEN, the second top-three finish on the trot.",
